# ⚡ Lightning Strikes EDA Mini Project

## 📌 Overview
This project performs Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) on a 2018 lightning strikes dataset using Python.  
The analysis focuses on identifying monthly lightning strike trends and visualizing the results with Matplotlib.

---

## 🛠️ Tools & Technologies
- Python
- Pandas
- Matplotlib
- Jupyter Notebook

---

## 📂 Dataset Columns
- `date` → Date of lightning strike
- `number_of_strikes` → Total lightning strikes
- `center_point_geom` → Geographic coordinates

---

## 📊 Project Workflow
✔ Data Loading  
✔ Data Cleaning  
✔ Feature Engineering  
✔ GroupBy Aggregation  
✔ Data Visualization  
✔ Insight Extraction  

---

## 🔍 Key Analysis
- Extracted month information from dates
- Grouped lightning strikes by month
- Calculated total strikes per month
- Built bar chart visualization for trend analysis

---

## 📈 Key Insights
- Lightning strikes were higher during mid-year months.
- Summer months showed peak lightning activity.
- Winter months had comparatively fewer strikes.

